title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\DataTransfer\V1\TransferRun
name: TransferRun
description:
Represents a data transfer run.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.datatransfer.v1.TransferRun

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The resource name of the transfer run. Transfer run names have the form projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}/transferConfigs/{config_id}/runs/{run_id}. The name is ignored when creating a transfer run.

params.name: data.schedule_time
params.description: Minimum time after which a transfer run can be started.

params.name: data.run_time
params.description: For batch transfer runs, specifies the date and time of the data should be ingested.

params.name: data.error_status
params.description: Status of the transfer run.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: Output only. Time when transfer run was started. Parameter ignored by server for input requests.

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Output only. Time when transfer run ended. Parameter ignored by server for input requests.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. Last time the data transfer run state was updated.

params.name: data.params
params.description: Output only. Parameters specific to each data source. For more information see the bq tab in the 'Setting up a data transfer' section for each data source. For example the parameters for Cloud Storage transfers are listed here: https://cloud.google.com/bigquery-transfer/docs/cloud-storage-transfer#bq

params.name: data.destination_dataset_id
params.description: Output only. The BigQuery target dataset id.

params.name: data.data_source_id
params.description: Output only. Data source id.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Data transfer run state. Ignored for input requests.

params.name: data.user_id
params.description: Deprecated. Unique ID of the user on whose behalf transfer is done.

params.name: data.schedule
params.description: Output only. Describes the schedule of this transfer run if it was created as part of a regular schedule. For batch transfer runs that are scheduled manually, this is empty. NOTE: the system might choose to delay the schedule depending on the current load, so schedule_time doesn't always match this.

params.name: data.notification_pubsub_topic
params.description: Output only. Pub/Sub topic where a notification will be sent after this transfer run finishes. The format for specifying a pubsub topic is: projects/{project}/topics/{topic}

params.name: data.email_preferences
params.description: Output only. Email notifications will be sent according to these preferences to the email address of the user who owns the transfer config this run was derived from.
